<br>
First of all, people would NOT SHUT UP!  The spam was horrendous and no one knew what was going on.  The raid leader was constantly telling people to be quiet but no one was listening to her.<br>
<br>
Pulls were awkward at first but started going better for awhile.  People finally got into the rhythm and it was going good.  But then it happened, a level 60 Druid who admitted to being Ebayed started claiming he could pull better.  His high level Paladin friend was backing him up and the two of them were annoying as hell.  I eventually put the Druid on ignore but couldn’t do the same with the Paladin (at the time I was still playing Islington and needed to know if a Paladin item dropped).  About the same time that pulls were going better people started to ask for mobs to get pulled.  Clerics were asking for Clerics of Inny to get pulled, Warriors wanted those mummy things, Shamans wanted their Golems etc.<br>
<br>
During this whole mess we didn’t get many armor pieces but we got lots of gems.  All higher level gems (diamonds, blue diamonds and the like) were being randomed first between the groups and then between the members of that group.  My group hadn’t won a single gem in about 12 drops and the group leader was being VERY loud about that fact.  We then get a kill and the leader loots a Diamond.  He immediately says to be quiet about it and we’re going to keep it.  At this point I send a tell to the raid leader telling her that a Diamond dropped and she blows up at the group leader.<br>
<br>
The final straw was the trains.  Idiots trained the camp 3 times in 30 minutes.  Everytime I managed to camp out but after the last one, a Druid friend of mine and I told the Raid Leader we were leaving.  She understood perfectly and we left.<br>
<br>
Anyway to the Bard rights issue:<br>
<br>
I agree with the majority of people here.  If it was agreed beforehand that a Bard could roll on a Cloak of the Flames then there should be no arguments or problems.  Make it clear before the Dragon run and there are no problems.<br>
<br>
Now I, personally, don’t think that a Bard really needs a Cloak of the Flames for the same reasons listed above.  Rangers, Monks, and Rogues can use this to increase their damage potential.  They do great damage and a COF will allow them to do even better.  Paladins and Shadow Knights are main tanks and a COF will allow them to taunt and maintain aggro better.  A Warrior is a combination of these two groups and will maximize the use of a COF.<br>
<br>
